      "term": "nonseriousness",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "null",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun",
          "definition": "the quality of not being serious; lack of seriousness or gravity",
          "examples": [
            "Her nonseriousness often made it hard to take her comments seriously.",
            "In his talk, the nonseriousness of the tone reduced the impact of the warning."
